The paper deals with algorithms design and inapproximability of Independent Set and related problems, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the study of graph structures and combinatorial optimization, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Moreover, the linear PCP conjecture, which is a major tool in the paper, is related to hardness of approximation and probabilistically checkable proofs, which are typical topics in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
